comment: /**  * Move the iterator to the next memory block. The next memory block starts at the first element that was not  * in the block before. A special case is when no record was in the block before, which happens when this  * function is invoked two times directly in a sequence, without calling hasNext() or next in between. Then  * the block moves one element.  *  * @return True if a new memory block was loaded, false if there were no further  *         records and hence no further memory block.  *  * @throws IOException Thrown, when advancing to the next block failed.  */
code: /**  * Move the iterator to the next memory block. The next memory block starts at the first element that was not  * in the block before. A special case is when no record was in the block before, which happens when this  * function is invoked two times directly in a sequence, without calling hasNext() or next in between. Then  * the block moves one element.  *  * @return True if a new memory block was loaded, false if there were no further  *         records and hence no further memory block.  *  * @throws IOException Thrown, when advancing to the next block failed.  */ public boolean nextBlock() throws IOException.
